<div class="min-h-screen bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-red-50">
  <nav class="bg-white shadow-sm">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="flex justify-between h-16">
        <div class="flex">
          <div class="flex-shrink-0 flex items-center">
            <a href="/" class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-600">Monado</a>
          </div>
          <div class="hidden sm:ml-6 sm:flex sm:space-x-8">
            <a href="/maybe" class="border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-700 inline-flex items-center px-1 pt-1 border-b-2 text-sm font-medium">
              Maybe Monad
            </a>
            <a href="/result" class="border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-700 inline-flex items-center px-1 pt-1 border-b-2 text-sm font-medium">
              Result Monad
            </a>
            <a href="/demo" class="border-transparent text-gray-500 hover:border-gray-300 hover:text-gray-700 inline-flex items-center px-1 pt-1 border-b-2 text-sm font-medium">
              Interactive Demo
            </a>
            <a href="/comparison" class="border-orange-500 text-gray-900 inline-flex items-center px-1 pt-1 border-b-2 text-sm font-medium">
              Before/After
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </nav>

  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <!-- Hero Section -->
    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
        Before & After Monads
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        See the dramatic difference monads make in real code
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Real Before/After Example -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Real-World Scenario</h2>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-6"><%= @before_after.scenario %></p>
      
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <!-- Before -->
        <div class="border-2 border-red-300 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl mr-3">üò∞</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-700">Without Monads</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
            <pre class="text-red-300 font-mono text-sm"><%= @before_after.without_monads %></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-red-800">
            <li>‚ùå 6 levels of nesting</li>
            <li>‚ùå Hard to follow the flow</li>
            <li>‚ùå Difficult to add new steps</li>
            <li>‚ùå Error handling scattered everywhere</li>
            <li>‚ùå Easy to miss edge cases</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- After -->
        <div class="border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-6">
          <div class="flex items-center mb-4">
            <span class="text-4xl mr-3">üòä</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700">With Monads</h3>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4">
            <pre class="text-green-300 font-mono text-sm"><%= @before_after.with_monads %></pre>
          </div>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-green-800">
            <li>‚úì Linear, easy-to-read pipeline</li>
            <li>‚úì Each step is independent</li>
            <li>‚úì Trivial to add/remove steps</li>
            <li>‚úì Consistent error handling</li>
            <li>‚úì Type-safe, compiler helps</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Improvements -->
      <div class="mt-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-teal-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">üéâ Improvements</h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
          <%= for improvement <- @before_after.improvements do %>
            <div class="flex items-start bg-white rounded-lg p-4 shadow">
              <span class="text-green-600 mr-2 text-xl">‚úì</span>
              <span class="text-gray-800"><%= improvement %></span>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <div class="overflow-x-auto">
        <table class="w-full">
          <thead class="bg-gray-50">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">Monad</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">Purpose</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">Success Type</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">Failure Type</th>
              <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left text-sm font-bold text-gray-900">Use When</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
            <tr class="hover:bg-purple-50 transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-purple-700">Maybe</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Handle optional values</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-purple-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">{:just, value}</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">:nothing</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Value might not exist, no error details needed</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-green-50 transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-green-700">Result</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Handle errors explicitly</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-green-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">{:ok, value}</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-red-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">{:error, reason}</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Operation can fail, need error context</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-blue-50 transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-blue-700">List</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Handle multiple values</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-blue-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">[values]</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-gray-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">[]</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Non-deterministic computations</td>
            </tr>
            <tr class="hover:bg-yellow-50 transition-colors">
              <td class="px-6 py-4 font-bold text-yellow-700">IO</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-700">Handle side effects</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4"><code class="bg-yellow-100 px-2 py-1 rounded text-sm">IO value</code></td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-gray-500 text-sm">N/A</td>
              <td class="px-6 py-4 text-sm text-gray-600">Side-effectful operations</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Detailed Comparisons -->
    <div class="space-y-8">
      <!-- Maybe vs Result -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Maybe vs Result: When to Use Which?</h2>
        
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
          <!-- Maybe Column -->
          <div class="border-2 border-purple-300 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-purple-700 mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-3xl mr-2">üéÅ</span>
              Maybe Monad
            </h3>
            
            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 mb-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>‚úì Finding items in collections</li>
              <li>‚úì Parsing simple values</li>
              <li>‚úì Optional configuration</li>
              <li>‚úì When failure reason doesn't matter</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Example:</h4>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-sm text-purple-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre># Find user by ID
users = %{1 => "Alice", 2 => "Bob"}

Map.get(users, 1) 
|> Maybe.return()
# {:just, "Alice"}

Map.get(users, 99)
|> Maybe.return()
# :nothing</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 bg-purple-50 rounded p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-purple-900">
                <strong>Key insight:</strong> Use Maybe when you just need to know "did we get a value or not?"
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Result Column -->
          <div class="border-2 border-green-300 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-green-700 mb-4 flex items-center">
              <span class="text-3xl mr-2">üìã</span>
              Result Monad
            </h3>
            
            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Best For:</h4>
            <ul class="space-y-2 mb-4 text-gray-700">
              <li>‚úì Validation with feedback</li>
              <li>‚úì File I/O operations</li>
              <li>‚úì Network requests</li>
              <li>‚úì When you need to know WHY it failed</li>
            </ul>

            <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Example:</h4>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-sm text-green-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre># Validate user age
validate_age = fn age ->
  cond do
    age < 0 -> 
      {:error, "Age cannot be negative"}
    age > 150 -> 
      {:error, "Age too large"}
    true -> 
      {:ok, age}
  end
end

validate_age.(25)  
# {:ok, 25}

validate_age.(-5)  
# {:error, "Age cannot be negative"}</pre>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-4 bg-green-50 rounded p-4">
              <p class="text-sm text-green-900">
                <strong>Key insight:</strong> Use Result when error details matter for debugging or user feedback!
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Side by Side Code Comparison -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Same Problem, Different Approaches</h2>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Let's solve the same problem (safe division) with different approaches:
        </p>

        <div class="space-y-6">
          <!-- Traditional Approach -->
          <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">‚ùå Traditional Approach (Not Recommended)</h3>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-red-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre>def divide(a, b):
    if b == 0:
        return None  # Lost information!
    return a / b

result = divide(10, 0)
if result is None:
    # Why did it fail? We don't know!
    print("Error!")</pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
              ‚ö†Ô∏è Problems: No error context, easy to forget null check, unclear intent
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Maybe Approach -->
          <div class="border-l-4 border-purple-500 pl-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">üéÅ Maybe Monad Approach</h3>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-purple-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre>def divide(a, b):
    if b == 0:
        return :nothing
    return {:just, a / b}

result = divide(10, 0)
case result:
    {:just, value} -> use_value(value)
    :nothing -> handle_failure()  # Type-safe!</pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
              ‚úì Benefits: Type-safe, composable, but no error details
            </p>
          </div>

          <!-- Result Approach -->
          <div class="border-l-4 border-green-500 pl-6">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">üìã Result Monad Approach (Best!)</h3>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded-lg p-4 font-mono text-sm text-green-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre>def divide(a, b):
    if b == 0:
        return {:error, "Division by zero"}
    return {:ok, a / b}

result = divide(10, 0)
case result:
    {:ok, value} -> use_value(value)
    {:error, reason} -> 
        log(reason)  # We know exactly what went wrong!
        handle_failure()</pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-2">
              ‚úì‚úì Benefits: Type-safe, composable, AND provides error context!
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Conversion Chart -->
      <div class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">Converting Between Monads</h2>
        
        <p class="text-gray-700 mb-6">
          Sometimes you need to convert from one monad to another:
        </p>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-100 to-green-100 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Maybe ‚Üí Result</h3>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-sm text-green-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre>Result.from_maybe(
  {:just, 42}, 
  "No value found"
)
# {:ok, 42}

Result.from_maybe(
  :nothing, 
  "No value found"
)
# {:error, "No value found"}</pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-3">
              Use when you need to add error context to a Maybe
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-100 to-purple-100 rounded-lg p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Result ‚Üí Maybe</h3>
            <div class="bg-gray-900 rounded p-4 font-mono text-sm text-purple-300 overflow-x-auto">
              <pre>result_to_maybe = fn
  {:ok, value} -> {:just, value}
  {:error, _} -> :nothing
end

result_to_maybe.({:ok, 42})
# {:just, 42}

result_to_maybe.({:error, "failed"})
# :nothing</pre>
            </div>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-700 mt-3">
              Use when you don't care about the error details
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Decision Tree -->
      <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-500 to-red-500 rounded-lg shadow-lg p-8 text-white">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Decision Tree: Which Monad Should I Use?</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-4 text-lg">
          <div class="flex items-start">
            <span class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 bg-white text-orange-600 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-3">?</span>
            <div>
              <strong>Can the operation fail or return nothing?</strong>
              <div class="ml-8 mt-2 space-y-2 text-base">
                <div class="flex items-start">
                  <span class="mr-2">‚ùå No</span>
                  <span class="text-orange-100">‚Üí Don't use a monad (or use Identity)</span>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <div class="flex items-start">
                    <span class="mr-2">‚úì Yes</span>
                    <span class="text-orange-100">‚Üí Continue...</span>
                  </div>
                  <div class="ml-8 mt-2 space-y-2">
                    <div class="flex items-start">
                      <span class="mr-2">‚Üì</span>
                      <span><strong>Do you need to know WHY it failed?</strong></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="ml-8 space-y-2 text-base">
                      <div class="flex items-start">
                        <span class="mr-2">‚ùå No</span>
                        <span class="text-orange-100">‚Üí Use <strong>Maybe</strong> monad</span>
                      </div>
                      <div class="flex items-start">
                        <span class="mr-2">‚úì Yes</span>
                        <span class="text-orange-100">‚Üí Use <strong>Result</strong> monad</span>
                      </div>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </main>

  <footer class="bg-white border-t border-gray-200 mt-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-8">
      <p class="text-center text-gray-500">
        Monado - Learning Monads Through Practice | Built with Phoenix & Elixir
      </p>
    </div>
  </footer>
</div>

